## 7. ARCHITECTURAL GUARDRAILS (MUST ENFORCE)

### 7.1 SSR Determinism
- **NO `Math.random()` in SSR paths** — currently 0 instances (verified P8)
- **NO `Date.now()` in SSR paths** — currently 0 instances (verified P8)
- All volatile/interactive content must be inside `"use client"` components
- Server components that fetch data use `export const dynamic = 'force-dynamic'`

### 7.2 Row Level Security
- **ALL 32 tables have RLS ENABLED** — verified P8
- Currently using `anon` role policies (read/write for all) — this is v2.0 demo-grade
- **v2.5 MUST upgrade to user-level RLS** keyed on `auth.uid()` with role-based access

### 7.3 Audit Log Immutability
- `audit_logs` table has 3 RLS policies: SELECT (anon), INSERT (anon), NO UPDATE, NO DELETE
- Any attempt to UPDATE or DELETE returns 0 rows affected
- The `writeAuditEntry()` function in `lib/audit.ts` is the ONLY way to write audit entries
- **NEVER create UPDATE/DELETE policies on audit_logs**

### 7.4 UI Standards
- **Tailwind CSS + Shadcn-UI ONLY** — no generic CSS, no external UI libraries
- Dark mode design system (slate-950 backgrounds, cyan/emerald/violet accents)
- All interactive elements must have unique IDs for testability
- Error boundaries: all components must fallback gracefully
- Responsive layout via PersonaLayout wrapper

### 7.5 Data Access Patterns
- Server components fetch data directly via `insforge.database.from('table').select()`
- Client components fetch via API routes (`/api/...`)
- **NEVER expose raw SQL to client** — all DB access goes through API routes or server components
- The `crm-service.ts` file contains shared data access functions

