## 8. KNOWN RISKS & TECHNICAL DEBT

| # | Risk | Severity | Description | Recommended Fix |
|---|------|----------|-------------|-----------------|
| 1 | Double journey activation | MEDIUM | No idempotency guard — activating same journey twice creates duplicate leads and execution records | Add `status` column check: block re-activation if already `completed` |
| 2 | No channel CHECK constraint | LOW | `marketing_fatigue_log.channel` accepts any string — no `CHECK (channel IN ('email','sms','push'))` | Add CHECK constraint via migration |
| 3 | Min 1 lead always spawned | LOW | `activate-journey` uses `Math.max(1, ...)` so at least 1 lead is created even with 0 reachable audience | Change to `Math.max(0, ...)` or add guard |
| 4 | Campaign rm_alerts have NULL FKs | LOW | Campaign-spawned RM alerts have `customer_id=NULL` and `case_id=NULL` — both are nullable FKs | Consider linking to first spawned lead or using a sentinel party |
| 5 | No DB indexes beyond PKs | HIGH | No custom indexes — queries will degrade at scale (10K+ rows) | Add indexes on frequently filtered columns (see v2.5 transition doc) |
| 6 | Schema files fragmented | MEDIUM | 3 separate SQL files: `schema.sql`, `schema_leads.sql`, `schema_refinement.sql` | Consolidate into numbered migrations directory |
| 7 | Single environment | HIGH | One `.env` file, one InsForge project — no dev/staging/prod separation | Create environment-specific configs |
| 8 | No automated tests | HIGH | Zero test files — all validation was manual/browser-based | Implement Jest + Playwright test suites |
| 9 | Customer/[id] 404 on staging | MEDIUM | Dynamic route `/customer/[id]` returns 404 on deployed staging site | Investigate Vercel dynamic route configuration |

